{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/lesser-known-html5-tricks","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"lesser-known-html5-tricks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lesser-known-html5-tricks\" aria-label=\"lesser known html5 tricks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lesser Known HTML5 Tricks:</h1>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"1editable-content\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1editable-content\" aria-label=\"1editable content permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1.Editable Content:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;h1 contentEditable&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>This feature lets you edit the content of element inside the browser just by clicking on the content. You must try!</p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"2-html-anchor-element-trick\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-html-anchor-element-trick\" aria-label=\"2 html anchor element trick permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. HTML anchor element trick:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;a href=”skype:username?chat”&gt;Start chat with the username&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=”skype:username?call”&gt;Start call with the username&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=”skype:username?add”&gt;Add username&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=”mailto:someone@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Send email&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=”tel:00000000”&gt;Make a call&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Here, just know I unfolded some of the things you can do with anchor tags that you may or may not be familiar with before reading this article. Well the good news is now you know these anchor element tricks!\n<br>\n<br></p>\n<h2 id=\"3refreshing-browser-after-a-specific-time\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#3refreshing-browser-after-a-specific-time\" aria-label=\"3refreshing browser after a specific time permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3.Refreshing browser after a specific time:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;meta http-equiv=”refresh” content=”10&quot;/&gt; </code></pre></div>\n<p>Using this meta code you can refresh your webpage in the iterval of every 10 seconds. Isn’t that super cool? You can use it to make your browser refresh every 5 seconds while you do your CSS. You don’t have to refresh your browser manually to see the changes.</p>\n<p><em>Note: you can set content value to any value you like and it will increase or decrease the seconds based on the given value.</em></p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"4-hiding-elements-without-the-help-of-css\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#4-hiding-elements-without-the-help-of-css\" aria-label=\"4 hiding elements without the help of css permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>4. Hiding elements without the help of CSS:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;h1 hidden&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Oh yess! Its true you can hide html elements without the help of CSS by using ‘hidden’ attribute. Also it doesn’t work like CSS hidden and what I mean by that is when we hide any element using attribute ‘hidden’ it works more like CSS “display: none” rather than “visibility: hidden”. It takes no space while CSS “visibility: hidden” only hides the element but still take up the space.</p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"5-html-prefetch-webpage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#5-html-prefetch-webpage\" aria-label=\"5 html prefetch webpage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>5. HTML prefetch webpage:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;link rel=”prefetch prerender” href=”” /&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>We know that after landing to the homepage the user is more likely to navigate to about page then you can prefetch the CSS files that will necessary for that webpage in the background before user even clicks on the link to navigate to that page. What it does is speeds up the process and user feels little to no delay in a reloading of a webpage.</p>\n<br>\n<br>\n<p><em>Happy Coding and Keep Reading, Cheers!</em></p>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Lesser Known HTML5 Tricks: 1.Editable Content: This feature lets you edit the content of element inside the browser just by clicking on the…","frontmatter":{"title":"Lesser Known HTML5 Tricks","date":"2020-10-28 21:16:09 +0530","categories":["html"],"tags":["HTML5","Web development","tricks"],"description":null,"keywords":"HTML5, Web development, tricks","author":"V Rahul","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/b470f7e2894cfeeffc06fe0270376933/02521/html.png","srcSet":"/static/b470f7e2894cfeeffc06fe0270376933/02521/html.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/lesser-known-html5-trick